# NextJS Project Structure Guidelines

## App Directory Structure
```
app/
├── (auth)/           # Authentication related routes
├── api/             # API routes
├── components/      # Shared components
│   ├── ui/         # UI components
│   └── forms/      # Form components
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
├── lib/            # Utility functions and configurations
├── styles/         # Global styles
└── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Component Guidelines
- Use kebab-case for component file names (e.g., `user-profile.tsx`)
- Place page-specific components in their respective page directories
- Keep shared components in the `components/` directory
- Use Server Components by default, only use Client Components when necessary

## File Naming Conventions
- Page files: `page.tsx`
- Layout files: `layout.tsx`
- Loading states: `loading.tsx`
- Error handling: `error.tsx`
- Route handlers: `route.ts`

## Best Practices
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Add loading states for data fetching
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow accessibility guidelines
- Optimize images using Next.js Image component
- Implement proper SEO meta tags
